# disabled

**Type Property**

An attribute indicating the disabled style.

## Declaration

```swift
static var disabled: UIMenuElement.Attributes { get }
```

## Discussion

When you use this attribute, the user can’t select the menu element.

## Attributes

- **destructive**: An attribute indicating the destructive style.
- **hidden**: An attribute indicating the hidden style.
- **keepsMenuPresented**: An attribute indicating that the menu remains presented after firing the element’s action instead of dismissing.
